HEADWORD: Confarreation
<hw>Con*far`re*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>confarreatio</ets>, fr. <ets>confarreare</ets> to marry;
<ets>con-</ets> + <ets>farreum</ets> (sc. <ets>libum</ets> cake) a spelt
cake, fr. <ets>farreus</ets> made of spelt, fr. <ets>far</ets> a sort of
grain.]</ety> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A form of marriage among the
Romans, in which an offering of bread was made, in presence of the high
priest and at least ten witnesses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confated</ent>⟦br⟧
